description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Locum Consultant General Surgeon with a Specialist Interest in Colorectal Surgery to join an innovative team dedicated to the delivery of high quality care within Sherwood Forest Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy general surgical unit, providing comprehensive emergency, in and outpatient diagnostic and treatment for colorectal, UGI, thyroid and endocrine patients serving a population of more than 400,000. You will help us to continue to provide a high quality service and maintain national cancer and 18 week referral to treatment targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a team player able to embrace change and modernisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a team which includes 11 Consultant General Surgeons plus visiting Consultants from Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust, 5 Speciality Doctors, a full junior medical team and 4 Specialist Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are active in the teaching of both Medical Students and Surgical Trainees as part of the Nottingham Medical School rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full GMC registration with a licence to practise and have had extensive experience in General Surgery and in particular Colorectal Surgery. The post holder will be able to demonstrate a wide range of skills and will be asked to work flexibly within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in some out of hours work will be expected and this will be remunerated as per terms and conditions set out in the Consultant contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post attracts 10 PA’s. Part time/job share applicants will also be considered. The post is offered on a fixed term contract for twelve months.&lt;/p&gt;
